articles.author: Joseph White, David Shepardson
articles.description: The United Auto Workers (UAW) union reached a tentative labor deal on Wednesday with Ford Motor (F.N), the first of Detroit's Big Three car manufacturers to negotiate a settlement to strikes joined by 45,000 workers since mid-September.
articles.title: Ford, UAW reach tentative deal to end strike including record pay raise

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China has stepped up spending to replace Western-made technology with domestic alternatives as Washington tightens curbs on high-tech exports to its rival, according to government tenders, research documents and four people familiar with the matter.
articles.title: China rushes to swap Western tech with domestic options as U.S. cracks down

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A rough year for Vietnam's real estate sector has seen developers miss interest payments on debt, amid a credit crunch spurred by ill-timed government measures, although spillover risk has been limited.
articles.title: Explainer: Vietnam's real estate woes: how much worse can they get?

articles.author: Stanley Widianto, Fanny Potkin
articles.description: TikTok and YouTube are considering joining Meta in applying for e-commerce licenses in Indonesia after Southeast Asia's largest economy banned online shopping on social media platforms, people familiar with the discussions said.
articles.title: Exclusive: TikTok, YouTube, Meta eye Indonesia e-commerce licenses- sources

articles.author: Tetsushi Kajimoto, Leika Kihara
articles.description: Japanese policymakers maintained their warning to investors against selling the yen on Thursday in the wake of the currency's renewed slide beyond 150 to the dollar, a level seen by traders as authorities' threshold for intervention.
articles.title: Japan policymakers jawbone markets as yen falls beyond key threshold

articles.author: Yu Xie, Alun John
articles.description: U.S Treasury yields were heading back towards 5% on Thursday, dragging shares around the world to multi-month lows in the middle of a busy week for corporate earnings, with an ECB meeting and the release of U.S. GDP to come later in the day.
articles.title: U.S. 10 year yield back near 5% puts more pressure on stocks

articles.author: Lewis Krauskopf
articles.description: Soaring U.S. Treasury yields are further boosting the appeal of bonds over stocks, deepening an already painful equity selloff while threatening to weigh on equity performance over the long term.
articles.title: Analysis: Soaring Treasury yields threaten long-term performance of US stocks

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Henriette Chacar
articles.description: Israel kept up its strikes on Hamas targets in Gaza as it prepared for a ground invasion while more Palestinian civilians were killed and world powers at the United Nations failed to secure plans to deliver critical humanitarian aid.
articles.title: Israel bombards Gaza, prepares invasion as Biden urges path to two states

articles.author: Luc Cohen
articles.description: Sam Bankman-Fried could take the stand at his fraud trial as soon as Thursday, when prosecutors are set to finish presenting their case accusing the founder of now-bankrupt cryptocurrency exchange FTX of stealing billions of dollars from customers.
articles.title: Sam Bankman-Fried could take stand at fraud trial over FTX collapse

articles.author: Robert Harvey, Natalie Grover
articles.description: U.S. penalties on shippers transporting Russian oil in breach of the G7's price cap could push more Russian cargoes onto vessels referred to as the ghost fleet and away from mainstream tankers, shipping sources and analysts told Reuters.
articles.title: World's ghost fleet in focus over US Russian price cap crackdown
